subject: p17327592
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there is again substantial elevation of the right hemidiaphragmatic contour. Opacification above this could reflect atelectasis, though in the appropriate clinical setting supervening pneumonia would have to be considered. Some prominence of the cardiac silhouette persists in a patient with intact midline sternal wires. No evidence of vascular congestion and the left lung is essentially clear.
